{
  "total_duration": 484.415,
  "lines": [
    {
      "i": 0,
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 15.6,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "想象客厅里摆着一件 1681 年做出来的老乐器。它像一个很早以前的小型键盘乐器，能发出安静的声音，可是比现代钢琴和电子键盘脆弱得多。家里人一直把它当成有历史的老物件。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 1,
      "start": 15.95,
      "end": 32.334,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的题目是"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Not for jazz"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，先别误会：这不是说"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "jazz"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "爵士乐不好。爵士乐可以有很强的节奏和很自由的表达，问题是这个老乐器承受不了那样用力的弹法。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 2,
      "start": 32.683,
      "end": 47.707,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "hook",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这个老乐器叫"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，可以理解成一种早期键盘乐器：外表有点像古老的小钢琴，但声音更轻，结构也更 delicate。它适合被小心地弹，不适合被当成现代键盘大力敲。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 3,
      "start": 48.057,
      "end": 71.193,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "1"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "故事先把主角摆出来："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We have an old musical instrument. It is called a clavichord."
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "instrument"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是用来演奏音乐的工具，比如 piano、guitar、violin、keyboard。这里的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是一个老式键盘乐器，不是玩具，也不是普通电子琴。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 4,
      "start": 71.543,
      "end": 95.086,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "2"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "接着课文讲它的来历："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It was made in Germany in 1681."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "它不是昨天买的新东西，而是从 1681 年来的古老物件。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Our clavichord is kept in the living room."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "它放在客厅里，就像家里的传家物、老相机、旧唱机或展示模型：看得见，但不等于随便玩。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 5,
      "start": 95.436,
      "end": 117.836,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "3"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这件乐器还很有家庭历史："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It has belonged to our family for a long time. The instrument was bought by my grandfather many years ago."
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "has belonged to"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "表示它一直属于这个家，连接过去和现在。被动句让我们一路看见：它被制造、被保存、被祖父买下。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 6,
      "start": 118.186,
      "end": 144.125,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "retell",
      "scene_meta": {
        "frame": "4"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "最近，转折来了："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Recently it was damaged by a visitor. She tried to play jazz on it!"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "重点不是“爵士乐错了”，而是她把一个脆弱的老乐器当成现代键盘用。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "She struck the keys too hard and two of the strings were broken."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "父亲很震惊。现在孩子们"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "are not allowed to touch it"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，乐器正在被父亲的朋友修理。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 7,
      "start": 144.475,
      "end": 151.283,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这一课最容易误会的地方，是题目"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "Not for jazz"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。它到底是什么意思？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 8,
      "start": 151.633,
      "end": 154.405,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是不是说 jazz 不好，或者太吵？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 9,
      "start": 154.755,
      "end": 166.33,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "不是。这里的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "jazz"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "只是一个有强节奏、很有表现力的音乐风格。真正的问题是 mismatch：演奏方式和乐器不匹配。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 10,
      "start": 166.68,
      "end": 170.881,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "就像不能拿爷爷的老胶片相机当手机乱点？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 11,
      "start": 171.231,
      "end": 184.311,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "对。老相机可以拍照，但不能像手机一样一直戳屏幕。旧唱机可以放唱片，但不能当蓝牙音箱拍来拍去。展示好的 LEGO 模型很好看，但不能随便拆。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 12,
      "start": 184.661,
      "end": 190.766,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "那"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "为什么不能直接翻成“古钢琴”就过去？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 13,
      "start": 191.116,
      "end": 205.076,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "因为学生可能以为它就是一台旧钢琴。更准确地说，它是早期 keyboard instrument，比现代钢琴更安静、更细、更脆弱。你可以想象一个家里的小型历史乐器，需要正确的手法和边界。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 14,
      "start": 205.426,
      "end": 209.421,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "课文里好多句子都像在讲这件东西的履历。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 15,
      "start": 209.771,
      "end": 231.758,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "很好，这就是今天的语法线索。故事不是先讲公式，而是把"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "当主角：它"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "is called"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "什么，在哪里"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "was made"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，被谁买下，怎么"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "was damaged"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，现在"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "is being repaired"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 16,
      "start": 232.108,
      "end": 235.97,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "所以被动语态像是在讲“物件的一生”？"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 17,
      "start": 236.32,
      "end": 249.96,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "discuss",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "正是。当我们更关心这个物件，而不是每一步是谁做的，就会自然用 passive voice。最后的意思是：这件乐器不是反对音乐，它只是 not for that kind of playing。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 18,
      "start": 250.31,
      "end": 253.262,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "passage_normal",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We have an old musical instrument."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
