        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 32,
      "start": 296.968,
      "end": 315.82,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "instrument"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "instrument"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“乐器”，也就是用来制造音乐的工具。piano、guitar、violin、drums 都是 instruments。课文里的"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "musical instrument"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "指的就是这件老式键盘乐器"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 33,
      "start": 316.169,
      "end": 318.921,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "damage"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第二个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "damage"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 34,
      "start": 319.271,
      "end": 320.879,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "damage"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "damage"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 35,
      "start": 321.229,
      "end": 343.108,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "damage"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "damage"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“损坏、伤害”。课文说"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "it was damaged by a visitor"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，不是说客人很坏，而是说她的使用方式不合适。她"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "struck the keys too hard"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，太用力按琴键，结果"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "two of the strings were broken"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "，两根琴弦断了。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 36,
      "start": 343.458,
      "end": 346.186,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "allow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "第三个词："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "allow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 37,
      "start": 346.536,
      "end": 348.048,
      "speaker": "B",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "allow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "allow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 38,
      "start": 348.398,
      "end": 365.63,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "vocab",
      "scene_meta": {
        "word": "allow"
      },
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "allow"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是“允许”。"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We are not allowed to touch it"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "意思是“我们不被允许碰它”。这个句子不是制造害怕，而是在建立 boundary：贵重、脆弱、有历史的东西，需要正确使用和清楚规则。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 39,
      "start": 365.98,
      "end": 416.018,
      "speaker": "A",
      "scene": "grammar",
      "scene_meta": {},
      "segments": [
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "今天的 grammar 可以叫“object life story”，物件的一生。普通主动句会问：谁做了这件事？但这篇更关心"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "clavichord"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "本身，所以句子都围着它走："
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It is called a clavichord."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是名字；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It was made in Germany in 1681."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是出生地和年代；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It is kept in the living room."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是现在的位置；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "The instrument was bought by my grandfather."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是家庭历史；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It was damaged by a visitor."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是事故；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "We are not allowed to touch it."
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "这是新规则；"
        },
        {
          "lang": "en",
          "text": "It is being repaired"
        },
        {
          "lang": "zh",
          "text": "是正在发生的修理。被动语态不是一张公式表，而是当“物件是主角”时，非常自然的讲故事方式。"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "i": 40,
      "start": 416.368,
